          <div class="faq-answer" style="display:none;padding:0 24px 20px;font-size:0.88rem;color:#666;line-height:1.75;">
            Yes. New direct applications are accepted if you meet the age (21–55), qualification (Diploma or 3 years experience), and income (RM3,000+/month) requirements, and pass the panel interview. RintiZ is one path to NGM, not the only path.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item fade-up" style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e8e8e8;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
          <button class="faq-btn" style="width:100%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:20px 24px;text-align:left;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;">
            <span style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:0.95rem;color:#111;">When do bonuses get paid?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-left:16px;transition:transform 0.25s;"><path d="M4 6.5L9 11.5L14 6.5" stroke="#999" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="display:none;padding:0 24px 20px;font-size:0.88rem;color:#666;line-height:1.75;">
            Monthly bonuses are paid via GIRO on the 15th of the following month, after AIA Elite Academy completes the validation exercise. A delay of up to 2 working days is permitted. No advance payouts, even if targets are hit early.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item fade-up" style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e8e8e8;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
          <button class="faq-btn" style="width:100%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:20px 24px;text-align:left;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;">
            <span style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:0.95rem;color:#111;">What exactly is AFYC?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-left:16px;transition:transform 0.25s;"><path d="M4 6.5L9 11.5L14 6.5" stroke="#999" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="display:none;padding:0 24px 20px;font-size:0.88rem;color:#666;line-height:1.75;">
            AFYC stands for Annualized First Year Commission. It's the annualised value of the commission you earn from selling Life, Family Takaful, and Personal Accident policies. Think of it as: if you sell a policy that generates RM1,000 in commission for the first year, that RM1,000 counts toward your AFYC. The bonus thresholds are set against your monthly AFYC figure.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item fade-up" style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e8e8e8;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
          <button class="faq-btn" style="width:100%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:20px 24px;text-align:left;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;">
            <span style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:600;font-size:0.95rem;color:#111;">What happens if I miss my monthly targets?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" style="flex-shrink:0;margin-left:16px;transition:transform 0.25s;"><path d="M4 6.5L9 11.5L14 6.5" stroke="#999" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" style="display:none;padding:0 24px 20px;font-size:0.88rem;color:#666;line-height:1.75;">
            Missing a monthly target means no bonus for that month — but you keep all commission earned from your sales. At the quarterly level, you have one safety net: a single Quarterly Retention Validation available once across the full 24 months. If you fail two consecutive quarters after exhausting the safety net, you exit the programme.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item fade-up" style="background:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e8e8e8;border-radius:12px;overflow:hidden;">
          <button class="faq-btn" style="width:100%;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:20px 24px;text-align:left;background:none;border:none;cursor:pointer;">
